Class BayesianProb

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ctk150230.BayesianProb

  • class BayesianProb
extends java.lang.Object

    BayesianProb

    This class creates a DataSet from a filename, calculates the class probabilities, and calculates the conditional probabilities of each attribute. Upon completion of the calculations the probabilities are output to the console The classProbabilities ArrayList contains the probabilities of a given data instance being classified as positive or negative. The conditionalProbabilities and negativeConditionalProbabilities LinkedHashMaps contain ArrayLists that the probabilities of an attribute being classified as positive/negative given that the data was classified as positive/negative. conditionalProbabilities is given that the overall data classification was positive and negativeConditionalProbabilities is given that the overall data classification was negative. The contained ArrayLists contain the conditional probabilities that the attribute itself is positive or negative.
    Since:
    2017-09-26
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Charles Krol
    See Also:
    DataSet, ArrayList, LinkedHashMap, IOException

        BayesianProb(java.lang.String filename)
      throws java.io.IOException
        Class constructor which initializes data structures used to calculate probabilities. Initializes a DataSet passing a filename to the constructor which parses the data file to store in the DataSet. It then calculates the probabilities and outputs the results to the console
        Parameters:
        filename - the name of the file containing the data to be trained with
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - the exception is from closing the BufferedReader and FileReader objects in the data set and the objects are checked before attempting to close them
